The House Committee on Ways and Means offers the following substitute to HB 357:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 7 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to imposition, rate, computation, exemption, and credits, so as to provide for tax
3 credits for certain contributions made by taxpayers to certain mortgage loan originators; to
4 provide for definitions; to provide for an aggregate annual limit; to provide for terms and
5 conditions; to provide for applications and certifications; to provide for the revocation of
6 qualified status; to provide for certain penalties; to provide for the promulgation of rules and
7 regulations; to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date and applicability;
8 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Article 2 of Chapter 7 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
12 imposition, rate, computation, exemptions, and credits, is amended by adding a new Code
13 section to read as follows:
14 "48-7-29.27.
15 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
