69 (B) A taxpayer that is preapproved for the tax credit allowed pursuant to this Code
70 section during the period provided for in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph shall only
71 be allowed such credit in an amount that shall not exceed 95 percent of the amount
72 otherwise allowed pursuant to this Code section.
73 (e)(1) Each qualified organization shall issue to each contributor a letter of confirmation
74 of contribution, which shall include the taxpayer's name, address, tax identification
75 number, the amount of the qualified contribution, the date of the qualified contribution,
76 and the total amount of the credit allowed to the taxpayer.
77 (2) To claim the tax credit allowed under this Code section, the taxpayer shall attach to
78 the taxpayer's tax return the letter provided for in paragraph (1) of this subsection. If the
79 taxpayer files an electronic return, such letter shall be required to be electronically
80 attached to the return only if the Internal Revenue Service allows such attachments to be
81 affixed and transmitted to the department. In the event the taxpayer files an electronic
82 tax return and such confirmation is not attached because the Internal Revenue Service
83 does not, at the time of such electronic filing, allow electronic attachments to the Georgia
84 tax return, such confirmation shall be maintained by the taxpayer and made available
85 upon request by the commissioner.
86 (3) The commissioner shall allow tax credits for any preapproved contributions made to
87 an exempted mortgage loan originator if such exempted mortgage loan originator was a
88 qualified organization at the time of the commissioner's preapproval of the contributions
89 and the taxpayer has otherwise complied with this Code section.
90 (f)(1) A taxpayer shall not be allowed to designate or direct the taxpayer's qualified
91 contributions to any particular purpose or for the direct benefit of any particular
92 individual.
93 (2) A taxpayer that operates, owns, or is a subsidiary of an association, organization, or
94 other entity that contracts directly with a qualified organization shall not be eligible for
