95 tax credits allowed under this Code section for contributions made to such qualified
96 organization.
97 (3) In soliciting contributions, no person shall represent or direct that, in exchange for
98 making qualified contributions to any qualified organization, a taxpayer shall receive any
99 direct or particular benefit. The status as a qualified organization shall be revoked for any
100 qualified organization determined to be in violation of this paragraph and shall not be
101 renewed for at least two years.
102 (g)(1) No qualified organization shall use more than 10 percent of qualified contributions
103 for administrative expenses or overhead. Each qualified organization shall maintain
104 accurate and current records of all expenditures of such funds and provide such records
105 to the commissioner upon request.
106 (2) A qualified organization that fails to comply with any of the requirements of this
107 Code section shall be given written notice by the department of such failure to comply
108 by certified mail and shall have 90 days from the receipt of such notice to correct all
109 deficiencies.
110 (3) Upon failure to correct all deficiencies within 90 days, the department shall revoke
111 the exempted mortgage loan originator's status as a qualified organization and such entity
112 shall be immediately removed from the department's list of qualified organizations.
113 (4) Each exempted mortgage loan originator that has had its status revoked pursuant to
114 this Code section shall immediately cease all expenditures of funds received pursuant to
115 this Code section and shall transfer all of such funds that are not yet expended to a
116 properly operating qualified organization within 30 calendar days of such revocation.
117 (h)(1) No credit shall be allowed under this Code section to a taxpayer for any amount
118 of qualified contributions that were utilized as deductions or exemptions from taxable
119 income.
120 (2) In no event shall the total amount of the tax credit under this Code section for a
121 taxable year exceed the taxpayer's income tax liability. No unused tax credit shall be
